race.comment: SUMMER'S LEGACY (2) finished off powerfully over 1400m last time out, settling out the back and ending up 1.7L off the winner at Ascot. The inside draw and rise in trip may see her be able to settle closer this time around which is a big tick. Ready to strike now third-up into the campaign. SHAULA (5) got the job done by 0.2L at Ascot last start in a CL1 when jumping the race favourite. Up to 1650m today, but that doesn't look an issue off what we saw last start and he maps to get every chance once again. Can repeat the dose. MODELISTIC (7) will be fitter for a couple of trials coming into her first-up performance and the mile looks ideal fresh. Include. SIDE SHOW (8) is building nicely this time in work and is not to be discounted.
